-- Nigerian Appeals Court Approves Sale of Union Bank, ThisDay Says
-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 2012-01-20T10:16:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/nigerian-appeals-court-approves-sale-of-union-bank-thisday-says.html
Nigeria ’s Court of Appeal in Lagos
gave permission to the central bank to sell Union Bank of
Nigeria Plc, one of eight lenders bailed out by the regulator in
2009, ThisDay  reported , citing the court’s judgment.  Justice Helen Ogunwumiju gave the ruling yesterday on an
appeal filed by some shareholders of Union Bank asking the court
to stop Lamido Sanusi, governor of the  Central Bank of Nigeria ,
from selling it, the Lagos-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
